Implement a way for inline text to be marked as unformatted.

This might be implemented using a triple brace markup.
{noformat}
e.g. {{{_This text should not be italicised_}}}
{noformat}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-8267].
  {panel}

Suggest that personal spaces be included in the list from getSpaces or at least an option be added to determine what type of spaces are to be returned.
See also http://developer.atlassian.com/jira/browse/TIMTAM-8

Here is the example: In space sp1, there is a page with content:

{code}
[root /etc]
{code}

After we move this page to space sp2, the content within that page changes to:

{code}
[sp2:root /etc]
{code}

Definitely and obviously, that kind of content change is not desired. And if that happens, it will be very cumbersome to manually correct those affected pages.

